---
layout: journal.njk
lang: "en"
title: "Third Place Japan Journal"
description: "Japan's dedicated third-place media — certifying spaces where you can simply be."
canonical: "/en/journal/"
hreflang_ja: "/journal/"
hreflang_en: "/en/journal/"
---
<section class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24">

  <div class="mb-16" data-aos="fade-up">
    <p class="label mb-4">Third Place Japan Journal — English</p>
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-light text-dark leading-tight mb-6">
      Places to simply<br>be.
    </h1>
    <div class="gold-rule mb-6"></div>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted max-w-xl">
      Third Place Japan certifies spaces across Japan where you can step out of your daily roles
      and simply exist. Cafés, hotels, spas, coworking spaces — evaluated through 7 original axes.
    </p>
  </div>

  {# Certified venues (English-available) #}
  {% set enVenues = venues | venuesWithEn %}
  {% if enVenues.length %}
  <div class="mb-20" data-aos="fade-up">
    <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-8">
      <p class="label">Certified Venues</p>
      <a href="/en/journal/certified/" class="text-xs text-muted hover:text-gold transition-colors">View all →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      {% for v in enVenues | sortByGrade | head(3) %}
      <a href="/en/journal/certified/{{ v.slug }}/" class="venue-card block p-6 bg-white hover:bg-ivory transition-colors group">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between mb-4">
          <span class="grade-badge">{{ v.grade }}</span>
          <span class="label">{{ v.category }}</span>
        </div>
        <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-light text-dark mb-2 group-hover:text-gold transition-colors">{{ v.name_en }}</h3>
        <p class="text-xs text-muted mb-3">{{ v.area_primary.area }}, {{ v.area_primary.prefecture }}, Japan</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-text leading-relaxed line-clamp-3">{{ v.citation_en }}</p>
      </a>
      {% endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
  {% endif %}

  {# What is a Third Place? #}
  <div class="border-t border-border pt-16" data-aos="fade-up">
    <p class="label mb-6">What is a Third Place?</p>
    <div class="max-w-xl">
      <p class="font-serif text-lg font-light text-dark leading-relaxed mb-4">
        A third place is neither home nor work — it is the space in between,
        where you are free from roles and obligations.
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-muted leading-relaxed">
        Third Place Japan certifies spaces that embody this quality across Japan,
        using 7 original evaluation axes: Comfort, Silence, Special Experience,
        Revisit Value, Inbound Accessibility, Shareable Moments, and Story.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Third Place Japan?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Third Place Japan is Japan's first certification platform for third places — spaces beyond home and work where people can simply be. TPJ evaluates cafés, hotels, spas, coworking spaces, and more using 7 original axes, awarding certifications from Certified to Flagship."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What are Japan's best third places?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "According to Third Place Japan, certified venues include spaces evaluated for comfort, silence, special experience, revisit value, inbound accessibility, shareable moments, and authentic story. Visit the certified venues list for the full selection."
      }
    }
  ]
}
</script>
